Package org.neo4j.bolt.runtime

Interface BoltResponseHandler

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MessageProcessingHandler, MutableConnectionState, ResultHandler
    public interface BoltResponseHandler
    Callback for handling the result of requests. For a given session, callbacks will be invoked serially, in the order they were given. This means you may pass the same callback multiple times without waiting for a reply, and are guaranteed that your callbacks will be called in order.
